  "body": "The shutdown is painfully slow when Nethermind has been running for a long time.\r\nHere is an example after 30+ days of uptime (on v1.17.0):\r\n```\r\n2023-04-01 18:34:32.5202|INFO|23|Closing DBs... \r\n2023-04-01 18:34:32.5202|INFO|23|Disposing DB Blocks \r\n2023-04-01 18:35:31.5590|INFO|23|Disposing DB State0 \r\n2023-04-01 18:36:26.8036|INFO|23|Disposing DB Metadata \r\n2023-04-01 18:37:10.6851|INFO|23|Disposing DB Bloom \r\n2023-04-01 18:38:38.7958|INFO|23|Disposing DB Headers \r\n2023-04-01 18:39:34.9636|INFO|23|Disposing DB Receipts \r\n2023-04-01 18:39:36.2464|INFO|23|Disposing DB Code \r\n2023-04-01 18:40:19.2184|INFO|23|Disposing DB Witness \r\n2023-04-01 18:40:19.2184|INFO|23|Disposing DB BlockInfos \r\n2023-04-01 18:41:13.6703|INFO|23|Disposing DB CanonicalHashTrie \r\n2023-04-01 18:41:13.6703|INFO|23|All DBs closed. \r\n2023-04-01 18:41:13.6703|INFO|23|Ethereum shutdown complete... please wait for all components to close \r\n2023-04-01 18:41:13.6703|INFO|23|All done, goodbye! \r\n\r\n```\r\nDuring this time the CPU is saturated by the Nethermind process (100% on all cores).\r\nThis causes some problems when Windows tries to shutdown for OS updates.\r\nPerformance is excellent otherwise on this specific hardware (i7-12700 + 32 GB RAM + Samsung EVO Plus SSD).\r\nUsing the default config file on mainnet.\r\n",
